# App Router

- Prefer Server Components when there is no need for client-only APIs (`useState`, browser-only APIs).
- Mark client components with `"use client"` only when required.
- Colocate feature UI under `app/<feature>/`; reuse shared logic from `lib/`.

# React

- Functional components; keep side effects explicit (`useEffect`) and dependencies correct.
- Extract hooks for reusable stateful logic (e.g. under `lib/hooks/`).
- Avoid heavy logic in JSX; compute in the component body or small helpers.

# Styling

- Use Tailwind / Hero UI patterns already in the project; avoid inline styles unless consistent with nearby code.

# Data from the client

- Call `app/api/*` or use Supabase clients through existing helpers — do not bypass auth or role checks that the API layer enforces.
